Sentencas: The performance stability and degradation mechanism of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) cathodes and LSCF impregnated Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-delta (LSCF-GDC) cathodes are investigated under solid oxide fuel cell operation conditions.
Titulo: Performance stability and degradation mechanism of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes under solid oxide fuel cells operation conditions

Sentencas: LSCF and LSCF-GDC cathodes show initially performance improvement but degrade under cathodic polarization treatment at 750 degrees C for 120 h.
Titulo: Performance stability and degradation mechanism of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes under solid oxide fuel cells operation conditions

Sentencas: The results confirm the grain growth and agglomeration of LSCF and in particular GDC-LSCF cathodes as well as the formation of SrCoOx particles on the surface of LSCF under cathodic polarization conditions.
Titulo: Performance stability and degradation mechanism of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes under solid oxide fuel cells operation conditions

Sentencas: The direct observation of SrCoOx formation has been made possible on the surface of dense LSCF electrode plate on GDC electrolyte.
Titulo: Performance stability and degradation mechanism of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes under solid oxide fuel cells operation conditions

Sentencas: The formation of SrCoOx is most likely due to the interaction between the segregated Sr and Co from LSCF lattice under polarization conditions.
Titulo: Performance stability and degradation mechanism of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes under solid oxide fuel cells operation conditions

Sentencas: The formation of SrCoOx would contribute to the deterioration of the electrocatalytic activity of the LSCF-based electrodes for the O-2 reduction in addition to the agglomeration and microstructure coarsening.
Titulo: Performance stability and degradation mechanism of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes under solid oxide fuel cells operation conditions
